    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-26T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="76"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0051/396: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-26T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 26, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1314. This is from Murphy. Your 1352, July 22, 9 p.m. I wish to assure the
                    Department that every effort will be made to obtain custody of accredited
                    civilian German officials. I am bringing this matter to the personal attention
                    of General Eisenhower and other members of the Allied Staff. It might be
                    mentioned that we had this matter very much in mind at the time of the Allied
                    landings in November when we hoped to seize person of the German Consul General
                    in Casablanca Theodore Auer. Due to the delay, however, in the landing of our
                    forces and the aid Auer received from a French official he succeeded in escaping
                    by motor car over the Spanish Moroccan frontier. [Murphy.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
